<br>
If it's the latter, then you have attacks bouncing back and forth between the 2 until one of them eventually misses the opponent as would naturally happen.  You'll have lots of attacks queued up and bounced back and forth, but it would reach a limit.<br>
<br>
For example suppose you only hit an average of 50% of the time (ignoring block, dodge, riposte, etc) and same for monsters.  If you swing once, you have a 50% chance to hit.  If that hits, then the mob will autoriposte, and have his 50% chance to hit.  If he hits you, then you autoriposte and have a 50% to hit on the riposte-riposte.  Repeat this process until one of those riposte attack rolls fails, or riposte disc drops.  The chance of your first attack being riposted is 50%.<br>
The chance of your first attack being successfully riposted back onto you is 25%.<br>
The chance of your first attack being successfully riposted back onto the mob is 12.5%.<br>
The chance of your first attack being successfully re-riposted back onto you is 6.25%.<br>
etc...<br>
Basicly, you won't have infinite attacks queued up, assuming that attacks can miss before they are autoriposted. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uquentislocksmythe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>QuentisLocksmythe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/3/02 8:46:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10579.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Double Counterattack?</span><hr size=1> It's easy to see from day-to-day fighting that if a mob ripostes your riposte, or you riposte it's, there is no hit and it stops right there.  It would be no different for using counterattack.  Every hit attempt would register a riposte for each of the participants, and that is all. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse>The Safehouse</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers>The Back Alley</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">The Safehouse website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.guildboss.com"><img
